        public boolean prerequisitesFulfilled()
        Checks if the prerequisites for running this experiment are currently fulfilled. Override this method if your experiment must do some form of setup before starting (e.g. generating files, etc.). Do not satisfy the prerequisites here: rather use fulfillPrerequisites().
        Returns:
        true if the prerequisites are fulfilled, false otherwise

                          throws ExperimentException

      • getDurationEstimate

        public float getDurationEstimate(float factor)
        Provides an estimate of the time this experiment is supposed to take. This value is used in the user interface to provide a rough measure of when a set of experiments is supposed to finish.
        Parameters:

      • mergeWith

        public boolean mergeWith(Experiment e,
                         boolean is_remote)
        Merges the output parameters and status of an experiment into the current one. This is only possible if the current experiment is not currently running.

        The following things in the current experiment will be overwritten by the same things in the experiment passed as an argument:

        • The experiment's status
        • All the output parameters
        • Any warnings generated during the execution
        • The progression indicator
        • The error message, if any
        • The start and end time
        • The "run by" string
        • The queuing status
        Parameters:
        e - The experiment to merge with
        is_remote - Set to true to indicate that e comes from a different instance of the lab. This will have for effect that if e is in state RUNNING, the current experiment will be set in state RUNNING_REMOTELY.
        Returns:
        true if the merge was done successfully, false if the merging was not done
